id: pm-g61e
title: "AGENTS.md: mandate reading full live pm item data (status/resolution/comments) before any state claim"
description: "Add a top-priority Non-Negotiable + Working Rule to AGENTS.md requiring agents to read the FULL current data of every relevant pm item (status, resolution, close_reason, expected/actual_result, all comments, notes, history) via pm get/pm comments BEFORE making or repeating ANY claim about its state, and to NEVER report a feature/release/fix/blocker as blocked/broken/working/done from memory, a prior summary, or a recalled system-reminder. Live pm data cross-checked against the real system (npm view, gh run/release list, workflow files) wins over stale memory. Trigger: in the 2026-06-30 PR#408 session the agent wrongly reported the daily auto-release as 'blocked (RELEASE_PAT absent)' from stale memory, when pm-9gxi was already CLOSED (RELEASE_PAT configured, v2026.6.30 published to npm latest + GitHub Releases). Prevents recurrence."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
